data.value:
CREDITS
First thanks to all donators! I did not thought that anybody would really donate for RED, but i turned out that quite a few people seem to like the app. But for now i removed the dontation button because i already have a bad feeling about
I removed the donation button for now - got enough donations :) THANK YOU VERY MUCH! If you want to appricate my work you can alternativly donate some money to other great open source projects or to the EFF. oss foundation, etc.
Sorry for not updating red for a long time - sorry I was just too busy with "real life"...
Special thanks to xxx and the computer club mesa for using RED
I'm sorry that RED requieres the .NET Framework, its really bloated, but actually i did not had the time to learn a mature programming language like c++. and da ja nowadays every windows comes with a .net...
DISCLAIMER
One user of RED reported that RED deleted folders that were not empty. I'm very sorry for that! I did check all my routines several times to be sure that nothing goes wrong, but somehow that happend. Da ich RED ursprnglich fr mich selbst entwickelt habe und es auch oft bentze habe ich besonders darauf geachtet die Funktionalitt sicher umzusetzen. I'm using RED myself, therefore I made everything as secure as I could) Sadly, i could never really determine what caused that behauvir. The user told me that the foldernames contained chinese charachters. So i tried to reproduce the error with chinese folder names but I could not reproduce the error. Theoretically RED should work fine with all sorts of special symbols. So be careful if you work with foldernames containing special characters, and if you bemerken irgendein problem send it to me. RED can alos contian traces spuren von nssen. The progam may also contain traces of nuts.
And sorry to all potential translators who offered me to translate RED into another language - till now i did not get the application ready for that.
For the moment the mehrsprachigkeit is off the table - english muss reichen. (RED is open source so, feel free to translate it yourself and send it to me or publish it elsewhere)
RED Is open source, so feel free to have a look how i made it, fork it, extend it, improve or ...
And too be honest: Da ich, wie bereits erwhnt versuche auf linux umzusteigen, (which is awsome) werde ich RED nur noch selten bentigen und vermutlich auch dei weiterentwicklung einschlafen. I'm also currently switching from windows to GNU/Linux - there is no RED* but it's a awsome open source project! * actually there is a similar tool named xxx that does the same ;) but the good thing with os ist that everybody can grab the code and cotninue my work. also wenn sich jmd von euch entschlossen fhlt red zu bernehmeen und weitezruwntickekln oder zu plefgen ann meldet euch.
